other_tests.findings: The patient appears uncomfortable, actively vomiting. Vital signs: Temp: 97.6, HR: 67, BP: 146/58, Resp: 20, O2 Sat: 100. Abdominal examination reveals soft abdomen with diffuse tenderness to palpation.
Appendix dilated to 14 mm with a hyperenhancing wall and adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute appendicitis. Small hiatal hernia noted, otherwise unremarkable findings in abdomen and pelvis.
